        <did>
            <unittitle>Raymond A. Ruge Ice Yacht Technical Drawings</unittitle>
            <unitdate normal="1902/1974" type="inclusive">1902 - 1974</unitdate>
            <abstract>Ice Yacht Technical Drawings designed by Raymond A. Ruge and E.A. Millenbach. Blueprints and tissue drawings from 1902 - 1974, primarily Hudson River Ice Yachts.</abstract>
            <physdesc>
                <extent>44 drawings in 3 roll boxes</extent>
            </physdesc>
            <langmaterial>
                <language langcode="eng">English</language>
            </langmaterial>
            <origination>
                <persname>Ruge, Raymond A.</persname>
            </origination>
            <repository>
                <corpname>Hudson River Maritime Museum</corpname>
                <address>
                    <addressline>50 Rondout Landing</addressline>
                    <addressline>Kingston, NY 12401</addressline>
                </address>
                <extptr xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://www.hrmm.org"/>
            </repository>
        </did>
        <accessrestrict>
            <p>This collection is open to researchers, by appointment, without restriction.</p>
        </accessrestrict>
        <bioghist>
            <p>Raymond A. Ruge, Ice Yacht Designer
E.A. Millenbach, Designer of 1947 Renegade II Ice Yacht</p>
        </bioghist>
        <controlaccess>
            <genreform authfilenumber="300034789" source="aat">technical drawings</genreform>
            <subject authfilenumber="sh2008124344" source="lcsh">Yachts--Design and construction</subject>
        </controlaccess>
        <scopecontent>
            <p>This collection contains 44 drawings in 3 roll boxes. Ice Yacht technical drawings by Raymond A. Ruge with six of 1947 Renegade II by E.A. Millenbach. Included are tissue, blueprint, construction details. Date range of 1902 - 1974 with majority in 1940s. Ice Yachts were used in the Hudson Valley, New York.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <userestrict>
            <p>Contact Hudson River Maritime Museum for copyright and use information.</p>
        </userestrict>
